{
  "stem": "1929.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they certainly knew that the consequence of being deported was something very bad.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was much more preferable to stay.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, she-- she just forces herself to go to the other line, where mother was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was very, very close to mother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she wanted to be with her.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Whatever the consequences were, she wanted to be with her.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She didn't want to be separated from her mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The next thing that I remember is that my brother, my father, and I went to this little factory, this barrel making factory.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there's names for it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can't-- I think it was the same day, but I cannot be certain.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well subsequently, we know that what happened was that the German were liquidating the ghetto, that they were deporting-- at this time, the ghetto was probably holding close to 25,000 to 30,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because a lot of those little villages like Soliev and the others-- the Jews were driven from there into Piotrkow, into the larger center.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And during this action, which took eight days, they would bring a train in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they would deport something like 6,000 people on the train, which was a cattle train.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they would drive 150 people into one of these cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They would be forced to leave all their possessions behind.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, there was-- from what I understand, it was, you know, terrible scenes, because mothers, and fathers, and children-- and also the old people, the older people who-- there were some people in the ghetto who could not-- who could not physically walk to the assembly place.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were paraplegic and they were people very sick in bed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the husbands wouldn't leave them, so the Gestapo and the Ukraine would shoot them.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
